Employee - Class in com.android
this class implements the cloneable interface which allows us to easily make copies of an object by creating an employee Employee emp1=new Employee(78.9,3459901) and create a new employee by going Employee emp2=emp1.clone() this creates a new employee emp2 which has the same weight and pps number but is a DIFFERENT employee if we did not implement the Cloneable interface we would not get a compilation error we would get a CloneNotSupportedException To see video tutorial for this section of code Video tutorial For all 177 videos, which cover all the topics in this course go to Complete Course Video Tutorial
